[normal]Written evidence from 
[normal]John Dwyer
[normal], 
[normal]Police and Crime Commissioner for Cheshire
[normal] [PCC Progress 05]
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I welcome the opportunity to contribute to the Home Affairs Select Committee’s second inquiry into Police and Crime Commissioners.   My submission is based around my own experience as a Police and Crime Commissioner in the areas the Committee has indicated it intends to address.  
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]The effectiveness of Commissioners in reducing crime and delivering an effective police service[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In Cheshire, I have been working closely with the Chief Constable and his senior leadership team to prevent and reduce crime.  Since the introduction of my Police and Crime Plan in April 2013, there have been over 1,000 fewer victims of crime in Cheshire and a 16% reduction in the number of re-offenders.  In September 2013, the Constabulary recorded the lowest volume of crimes for many years and victim satisfaction with the overall service received has increased to 89%, the fourth highest nationally.   
[normal] 
[normal]I have also robustly challenged the Chief Constable in areas where I believe there is a need for improvement.  For instance, I ha
[normal]d
[normal] some concern regarding the rate of detections for bur
[normal]glary dwelling offences and
[normal] commissioned HMIC to conduct a formal rev
[normal]iew of
[normal] burglary investigations.
[normal]  As a result of this
[normal],
[normal] the Constabulary introduced more rigour to the process which has positively contributed to the crime and detection figures.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I have worked with the Constabulary to introduce strategies which tackle issues highlighted within my 
[normal]Police and Crime 
[normal]Plan, for instance a Mental Health Strategy and a Rural, Heritage and Wildlife Crime Strategy. 
[normal]The Mental Health Strategy will increase the confidence and skills of front line officers in dealing with mental health incidents and use this information with the health service, Mental Health Trusts and local authority partners to develop better pathways to help individuals with mental health needs. For those with acute needs, the focus is on ensuring that they are assessed in appropriate places of safety, particularly when under the influence of alcohol and drugs.  The Rural Crime Strategy will ensure that an effective, efficient and proportionate response is provided to crimes and incidents affecting rural communities and Cheshire’s wildlife and heritage assets.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In terms of delivering an efficient police service, upon taking up office, I instigated a root and branch review of all aspects of policing in Cheshire.  This review has highlighted 
[normal]areas for 
[normal]s
[normal]ignificant savings including
[normal]: re-evaluating building agreements, procurement of uniforms and diesel for the fleet. The review has also led to a new model of policing being designed.  This will focus on local neighbourhood policing with the right capacity and capabilities to meet the 
[normal]public’s demand
[normal],
[normal] supported by lean central capabilities. This emerging model has been costed at £17 million below current costs
[normal].  It 
[normal]will make a significant contribution to the £3
[normal]4
[normal] million savi
[normal]ngs required over the next four
[normal] years
[normal], whilst protecting frontline policing and enabling some police officer recruitment to take place. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I am not complacent and will be seeking further opportunities to increase efficiency and improve services during my term in office.  The transfer of funding to Police and Crime Commissioners to commission services for victims offers a real opportunity for us to put victims at the heart of the criminal justice system and ensure that victims no longer fall through the cracks as has happened in the past.  
[normal]Through my engagement with the public
[normal].  I have been
[normal] informed of cases where victims do not appear to have received an appropriate standard of service from the police or criminal justice partners.  As an elected representative of the people of Cheshire, I have challenged the relevant agency in such cases to ensure that lessons are learnt for the future.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The role of the Commissioner in holding the Chief Constable to account[bold]&#xa0;[bold]6)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I have introduced robust mechanisms to ensure that the Chief Constable is effectively held to account on behalf of the people of Cheshire.  Public 
[normal]Scrutiny M
[normal]eetings are held on a quarterly basis at which the Chief Constable is held to account for performance against the objectives within the Police and Crime Plan and for other aspects of service delivery including financial performance, complaints and human resources.  These meetings are supplemented with monthly private sessions at which I am able 
[normal]to 
[normal]scrutinise a broader range of more sensitive operational performance matters.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I have also appointed a Deputy Commissioner, the former Independent Chairman o
[normal]f the Police Authority, who has
[normal] vast experience in holding the police to account.  The Deputy Commissioner’s portfolio includes in depth scrutiny of human resources, complaints, 
[normal]and 
[normal]protective services areas of policing
[normal].  D
[normal]ip sampling of completed complaints files, firearms incidents, and public order incidents
[normal] is undertaken by the Deputy Commissioner
[normal].  I believe that the scrutiny mechanisms which have been introduced provide me with a good understanding of the Constabulary’s performance and have helped contribute to the reductions in crime referred to above.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The role of the Police and Crime Panel in scrutinising the Commissioner [bold]&#xa0;[bold]8)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I have sought to build a positive and constructive working relationship with the Police and Crime Panel in Cheshire.   I am committed to personally attending Panel meetings so that the Panel can hold me to account for the totality of policing in Cheshire.  The agenda papers for Decision and Scrutiny Meetings are available via my website so the Panel has easy access to the decisions I have made and the information used to hold the Chi
[normal]ef Constable to account.  Staff 
[normal]within my office have provided the officers who support the Panel with training so they are able to interpret the performance data which is considered.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Members of the Panel regularly attend Scrutiny Meetings to observe the Chief Constable being held to account
[normal], the Members provide written feedback
[normal] 
[normal]to the 
[normal]Panel 
[normal]which gives 
[normal]a greater understanding of the challenges faced by the Constabulary and reassurance that I am fulfilling my statutory functions.   I have recently held an informal briefing with the Panel to outline the emerging findings from the root and branch review.  This event was productive and useful for both parties and I have now extended an invitation to the Panel to meet with me informally every six months. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The division of staff and functions and staff between the Commissioner and Chief Constable following the stage 2 transfer[bold]&#xa0;[bold]10)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Intensive discussion took place with the Chief Constable over the Summer to agree the shape of the Stage 2 transfer in Cheshire.  Our discussions were based around a set of locally agreed key principles for the transfer which included: 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]11)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Transfer Scheme which I have submitted meets both the locally agreed transfer principles and those outlined by the Home Secretary. The Stage 2 Transfer Scheme which is currently awaiting the Home Secretary’s determination provides that:  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
